Text.Value: You're on the right track with Flame Cullagh. He might be some use to us after all.
I can see that. But progress is progress.
Looks like the stump had some life in him yet - well done.
Heard you're meant to be heading toward the Towers.
I'd rather lend you my blade, but you'll have to make do with my luck.
We ought to be doing just that. Not babysitting this stump.
You heard right.
'A good soldier knows when he isn't the man for the job.' So sayeth Florrick.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a bit of a bitter edge. He's not super pissed, but isn't happy.

Text.Value: Don't let me hold you up. You've got a curse to clear.

EditorData.logicalname: Player is WIP clearing curse with Halsin

Text.Value: And yet - orders are orders.
I'm not as hopeful as Florrick. For my money, we're better off strategising without him.
It's not over yet.
Looks like you might actually finish what we couldn't. I'm impressed.

EditorData.logicalname: Player is WIP clearing curse with Halsin

Text.Value: Thank you.

EditorData.NodeContext: hint of sarcasm, but just a hint

Text.Value: Doing your job, you mean.
Leave.
If you find us a way into the Towers, we'll be there, shield to shield. Until then... we wait.
Heard you're working on a way in yourselves.
I'm glad you're enjoying spectating.
I answer to Florrick. And she's told me to stand guard.
That's right - but I've heard this bedridden fellow might be able to help.
That makes you our best bet. Hope it's a good one.
You've got a long road ahead of you yet. I wish you luck.
You're welcome.
Not sure I'd call it that myself. This fellow's in no condition to help anyone.
With a single word, Florrick could charge the Coast's most powerful force with taking back the Grand Duke.

Synopsis: The Flaming FIst Manip, Vidor, has conflict with Florrick prior to any of these dialogues. He is the sergeant of the FF troops, and believes Florrick is a terrible leader. Player can respond to his idea that he should attack Moonrise.
